parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent loss of vehicle control can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle hits a small bump or lump in the road, leading to a loss of steering control.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a sudden loss of control when hitting a small bump or lump in the road
making it difficult to steer
and the problem occurs intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incorrect welding of the flange on the rear axle housing can cause the U-bolts to be too short, leading to a loss of vehicle stability and control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience unusual vibrations
noise
or difficulty steering
and the rear axle housing may show signs of wear or damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden jerk of the steering wheel to either left or right can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and can lead to a loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel jerks to either left or right
making it difficult to steer
and the problem may occur suddenly and without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control module can cause the vehicle to catch fire, potentially resulting in property damage, injury, or even loss of life.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
often after sitting idle for an extended period
with no apparent warning signs or symptoms.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, potentially resulting in property damage, injury, or even loss of life.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
often with no apparent warning signs or symptoms.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or run rough, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or runs rough
the fuel pump fails to provide adequate fuel pressure
the vehicle experiences difficulty starting or maintaining speed
the fuel pump makes unusual noises or produces excessive heat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Rupture due to Fender Splash Guard Interference
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rupture of the brake line can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a failure of the braking system, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
brake fluid leak
loss of brake pressure
grinding or screeching noise when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front End Shimmy on Ford F-Super Duty Chassis
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The violent shimmy or vibration of the front end can cause loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle and its contents.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle experiences a tremendous shimmy or vibration when hitting raised spots or chuckholes on the highway
requiring the driver to slow down to almost a complete stop to regain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Caliper Failure due to Worn Brake Pads
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can lead to a loss of braking effectiveness, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: When brake pads wear down to 50%
the caliper strikes the spring
destroying the effectiveness of the brakes.
